---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/styles.css';

// Define the weeks data directly for now
const weeks = [
    { number: 0, title: "S3tup & 0nb04rd1ng", subtitle: "Environment Configuration - Dev tools mastery", status: "available" },
    { number: 1, title: "Th3 F1r5t T4g", subtitle: "Single Tag Mastery - Understanding HTML anatomy", status: "loacked"},
    { number: 2, title: "D0cum3nt 4rch1t3ctur3", subtitle: "Structure Before Style - Valid HTML foundations", status: "locked" },
    { number: 3, title: "Th3 C4sc4d3 B3g1n5", subtitle: "CSS Separation of Concerns", status: "locked" },
    { number: 4, title: "F0rm5 & 1nput5", subtitle: "User Interaction Patterns", status: "locked" },
    { number: 5, title: "Fl3xb0x M45t3ry", subtitle: "One-dimensional Layouts", status: "locked" },
    { number: 6, title: "Tr1but3 P4g3", subtitle: "First Complete Project", status: "locked" },
    { number: 7, title: "Gr1d Sy5t3m5", subtitle: "Two-dimensional Thinking", status: "locked" },
    { number: 8, title: "Pr0duct L4nd1ng", subtitle: "Professional Product Page", status: "locked" },
    { number: 9, title: "P0rtf0l10 Sy5t3m", subtitle: "Personal Brand Development (2 weeks)", status: "locked" },
    { number: 11, title: "Sh1p 1t", subtitle: "Launch & Deploy", status: "locked" }
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Home - DESN368">
    <main class="course-content two-column">
        <div class="main-content">
            <!-- Course Introduction -->
            <section class="card">
                <h2>Welcome to the Real Thing</h2>
                <p>Most people live on the surface of the web—scrolling, clicking, tapping. But beneath all of that, there's structure. Logic. Craft.</p>
                
                <p>In this class, you'll learn to read and write the source code that powers the modern internet. Not with drag-and-drop tools. Not through shortcuts. But with the foundational tools—HTML and CSS—the way it actually works.</p>

                <p>You'll start from nothing. Build from scratch. And by the end, you won't just have a few websites. You'll have a lens—a way of seeing and shaping digital space that most people never access.</p>

                <p><strong>This isn't a bootcamp. This isn't a YouTube tutorial. This is the real thing.</strong></p>
            </section>

            <!-- Student Pledge -->
            <section class="card">
                <h2>Student Pledge</h2>
                <div class="code-block">
                    "I will not blindly copy and paste.<br>
                    I will write my own tags.<br>
                    I will read the source.<br>
                    I will not fear the browser inspector.<br>
                    I will know what my code does.<br>
                    I will build with intent."
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Course Structure -->
            <section class="card">
                <h2>Course Structure: 11 Weeks of Foundation</h2>
                <div class="week-list">
                    {weeks.map((week) => (
                        <div class="week-item">
                            <div>
                                <h3>
                                    {week.status === "available" ? (
                                        <a href={`/weeks/week-${week.number}`}>
                                            Week {week.number}: {week.title}
                                        </a>
                                    ) : (
                                        `Week ${week.number}: ${week.title}`
                                    )}
                                </h3>
                                <p>{week.subtitle}</p>
                            </div>
                            <span class={`week-status status-${week.status}`}>
                                {week.status === "available" && week.assignments 
                                    ? `${week.assignments} Assignments` 
                                    : week.status === "available" 
                                    ? "Available"
                                    : "Coming Soon"}
                            </span>
                        </div>
                    ))}
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Brick by Brick Method -->
            <section class="card">
                <h2>The "Brick by Brick" Method</h2>
                
                <h3>Micro-Skills Architecture</h3>
                <p>Each assignment builds one tiny, specific skill that becomes the foundation for the next. You cannot proceed to Assignment B until you demonstrate mastery of Assignment A through multiple assessment gates.</p>
                
                <h3>Four Types of Mastery Gates</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Technical Gate</strong> - Code validates and works perfectly</li>
                    <li><strong>Conceptual Gate</strong> - Can explain why it works</li>
                    <li><strong>Debug Gate</strong> - Can fix broken code</li>
                    <li><strong>Teaching Gate</strong> - Can help a classmate understand</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>No Student Left Behind</h3>
                <p>Multiple learning pathways accommodate different learning styles:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Visual learners:</strong> Figma integration and visual diagrams</li>
                    <li><strong>Kinesthetic learners:</strong> Hands-on coding from day one</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytical learners:</strong> Deep documentation and technical specs</li>
                    <li><strong>Social learners:</strong> Peer teaching and pair programming</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Why This Works</h3>
                <p>Traditional courses throw everything at you at once. You memorize, you forget. This course builds muscle memory. Each micro-skill becomes automatic before you move on. By Week 11, you won't have to think about syntax—your fingers will know.</p>
            </section>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar">
            <!-- Quick Actions -->
            <section class="card">
                <h3>Quick Actions</h3>
                <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <a href="/weeks/week-0" class="btn btn-primary">Start Week 0</a>
                    <a href="/syllabus" class="btn btn-secondary">View Syllabus</a>
                    <a href="https://github.com/sicxz/desn368-f25" class="btn btn-secondary">GitHub Repo</a>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Course Tools -->
            <section class="card">
                <h3>Required Tools</h3>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                        <strong>Text Editor:</strong> VS Code
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                        <strong>Browser:</strong> Chrome DevTools
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                        <strong>Validation:</strong> W3C Validators
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                        <strong>Version Control:</strong> Git & GitHub
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                        <strong>Design:</strong> Figma (optional)
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <!-- Philosophy Quote -->
            <section class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--ewu-red); font-style: italic;">
                <p>"We're not making pretty pages.<br>We're building digital infrastructure."</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Resources -->
            <section class="card">
                <h3>Resources</h3>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; font-size: 13px;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/">MDN Web Docs</a>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <a href="https://validator.w3.org/">W3C Validator</a>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <a href="https://css-tricks.com/">CSS-Tricks</a>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <a href="https://codepen.io/">CodePen</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </aside>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>